3:["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"KuCoin calculates FET/USDT funding rates every 8 hours at 00:00, 08:00, and 16:00 UTC using a time-weighted average premium index. The exchange caps funding rates at ±0.75% per interval to prevent extreme payouts. Position holders pay or receive funding based on their long/short exposure at settlement time. KuCoin's moderate perpetual liquidity means funding rates can swing more dramatically during AI sector hype cycles compared to major tokens."}]
4:["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":["Why ","FET","/","USDT","?"]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"FET represents the artificial intelligence narrative in crypto, experiencing high volatility during AI-related market cycles. The token's mid-tier trading volume on KuCoin creates opportunities for elevated funding rates during trending periods. AI tokens like FET often see asymmetric funding patterns as retail traders favor long positions during technology hype phases."}]]}]
5:["$","section","0",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Historical FET Funding Rate Patterns"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"FET funding rates on KuCoin have shown strong correlation with AI sector sentiment and ChatGPT adoption cycles. During Q1 2023's AI boom, FET perpetuals frequently commanded positive funding rates above 0.1% per 8-hour cycle. The token exhibits seasonal patterns where funding rates spike during AI conference seasons and major partnership announcements. Weekend periods often see reduced funding volatility due to lower institutional activity in AI token trading."}]]}]
6:["$","section","1",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"KuCoin FET Arbitrage Opportunities"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"KuCoin's FET perpetual typically trades at higher funding rates compared to tier-1 exchanges during bullish AI cycles, creating cross-exchange arbitrage potential. The exchange's maker fee of 0.02% allows for profitable arbitrage when funding rate differences exceed 0.08% per cycle. Traders can exploit KuCoin's slower price discovery by maintaining opposing positions across exchanges. The platform's decent altcoin liquidity supports moderate position sizes without significant slippage impact."}]]}]
7:["$","section","2",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Risk Management for FET Positions"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"FET's high beta to AI sector sentiment requires careful position sizing and stop-loss management on KuCoin. The token's relatively small market cap creates susceptibility to whale manipulation and sudden funding rate reversals. KuCoin's moderate liquidity depth means large positions may face execution risks during volatile periods. Traders should monitor correlation with major AI stocks and adjust exposure accordingly, as FET often follows traditional AI equity movements with amplified volatility."}]]}]
8:["$","$Ld",null,{"items":[{"question":"What are typical FET funding rates on KuCoin during AI market cycles?","answer":"During AI hype cycles, FET funding rates on KuCoin commonly range from 0.05% to 0.25% per 8-hour period, with peaks reaching 0.5% during extreme bullish sentiment. Bear markets typically see rates between -0.05% to 0.05%."},{"question":"How does KuCoin's FET perpetual liquidity compare to other exchanges?","answer":"KuCoin offers moderate FET perpetual liquidity with typical order book depth supporting $10K-50K trades without significant slippage. This is lower than Binance or OKX but sufficient for most retail arbitrage strategies."},{"question":"Can I use KuCoin's trading bots for FET funding rate strategies?","answer":"Yes, KuCoin's trading bot marketplace includes grid and DCA bots that can be configured for funding rate arbitrage strategies. However, manual oversight is recommended due to FET's volatility and funding rate sensitivity to AI sector news."},{"question":"What are the main risks of FET funding arbitrage on KuCoin?","answer":"Primary risks include FET's high volatility overwhelming funding gains, KuCoin's regulatory uncertainties affecting withdrawals, and the token's correlation with broader AI sentiment creating directional exposure. Position sizing should account for potential 20%+ daily moves."}]}]
